# === NETWORK SECURITY (blocking via named set — security_ai.rs) ===
# The nftables blocklist set `lifeos_banlist` is pre-created by
# /etc/firewalld/zones/lifeos.xml (or the nftables ruleset). To blackhole a
# source address, Axi adds/removes elements to this set only — no raw rule
# creation allowed.
%wheel ALL=(root) NOPASSWD: /usr/sbin/nft add element inet filter lifeos_banlist { *
%wheel ALL=(root) NOPASSWD: /usr/sbin/nft delete element inet filter lifeos_banlist { *
# (No /usr/sbin/iptables -A INPUT wildcard — iptables blocking deprecated.)

